@title Welcome to the official documentation of the Ceylan-Mobile API

@doc <h3>Overview</h3>

<p>`Ceylan-Mobile' is a library allowing to <b>control mobile phones and 3G keys from Erlang</b>.
</p>

<p>This website presents the documentation of the API (<em>Application Programming Interface</em>) of Mobile version PROJECT_VERSION (as of GENERATION_DATE).
</p>

<p>
<b>Note that, currently, code based on Seaplus is not correctly taken into account by edoc</b>, which cannot detect any code added by a parse transform (typically, here, the code generated by Seaplus, based on the Mobile-specified function specs) or even the functions that are overridden explicitly by Mobile (as edoc is not aware that actually that they will be exported). However the full Mobile codebase <em>is</em> intensely documented, refer to <a href="https://github.com/Olivier-Boudeville/Ceylan-Mobile/tree/master/src" target="_blank">this repository</a> for full information.
</p>

<p>Ceylan-Mobile relies on the <a href="http://seaplus.esperide.org" target="_blank">Seaplus bridge</a> (to control the C code of <a href="https://docs.gammu.org/c/api.html" target="_blank">Gammu</a> from Erlang) and on the <a href="http://myriad.esperide.org" target="_blank">Myriad layer</a> (as a generic Erlang toolbox).
</p>


